      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Many of the Unicode Converter functions that perform conversions require a Unicode converter object containing information used for the conversion process. There are three types of Unicode converter objects used for different types of conversions. You use the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "UnicodeToTextInfo",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " type, described here, for converting from Unicode to text.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Because your application cannot directly create or modify the contents of the private Unicode converter object, the Unicode Converter provides functions to create and dispose of it. To create a Unicode converter object for converting from Unicode to text, your application must first call either the function ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coreservices/1433522-createunicodetotextinfo",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " or ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coreservices/1433550-createunicodetotextinfobyencodin",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". ",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can then pass this object to the function ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coreservices/1433542-convertfromunicodetotext",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " or ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coreservices/1433581-convertfromunicodetopstring",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to identify the information used to perform the actual conversion. After you have finished using the object, you should release the memory allocated for it by calling the function ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coreservices/1433564-disposeunicodetotextinfo",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A Unicode converter object for this purpose is defined by the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "UnicodeToTextInfo",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " data type.  ",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
